    "content" : "I've just put the stock reduction box gearbox in my bus \n<br>it was previously straight axled with a 'late' style thrust bearing\n<br>\n<br>the stock box has an 'early' style thrust bearing and what ~i consider a late style clutch (i.e, not the clutch with 3 arms…but lots of smaller prongs\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>the clutch works…but I really need to wind the cable all the way down, so the lever on the gearbox is pulling all the time…and nearly reaching the end of its travel before the thrust bearing engages the clutch\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>have I done something wrong, do these 2 styles work together ??\n<br>\n<br>thrust bearing style\n<br>\n<!-- m -->\n<a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/VW-Beetle-Camper-Clutch-Release-Bearing-Early-Type-Thrust-T1-T2-Bug-Bus-Bay-/181254612115?pt=LH_DefaultDomain_3&amp;hash=item2a339de493\">http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/VW-Beetle-Cam ... 2a339de493</a>\n<!-- m -->\n<br>\n<br>clutch style\n<br>\n<!-- m -->\n<a class=\"postlink\" href=\"http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/SACHS-CLUTCH-KIT-FLYWHEEL-3000951790-/231243927354?pt=LH_DefaultDomain_3&amp;fits=Model%3ANew+Beetle&amp;hash=item35d7364f3a\">http://www.ebay.co.uk/itm/SACHS-CLUTCH- ... 35d7364f3a</a>\n<!-- m -->",
